sql:
SELECT incident_type, COUNT(*) AS Total_Incidents
FROM safety_incidents
GROUP BY incident_type;

SELECT aircraft.model, missions.mission_status
FROM missions
JOIN aircraft ON missions.aircraft_id = aircraft.aircraft_id;

external_knowledge:
"Lengthy maintenance periods" refers to an average maintenance duration greater than 30 hours. "Recent missions" refers to those involving aircraft that had maintenance carried out within the last year. "Beyond routine checks" implies extensive or significant maintenance work. ;
An average maintenance duration greater than 30 hours is considered extensive. ;
The query focuses on aircraft that are in an 'active' status and had maintenance performed within the last year.

- 'service team' refers to users with the role 'maintenance crew'.;
- The term 'missions' in this context involves specific tasks, such as maintenance, assigned to aircraft.;
- 'Completed missions' are those that have reached their end status, indicating successful completion.;
